column11: The data you carry is vital to the remaining Federation fleet. You'll need supplies for the journey, so make sure to explore each sector before moving on to the next. But get to the exit before the pursuing Rebel fleet can catch up!  TIP: Upgrades -  Don't forget to upgrade your ship! Often shields are the highest priority, but don't underestimate the usefulness of subsystems.
With the pirates gone you signal the station. We appreciate what you've done, but there'll just be another ship looking to profit from our isolation soon enough. Sorry we can't give you more.
The pirate's victim quickly jumps away before you have a chance to speak to them.
Their ship breaks apart and you are relieved to know that you are still one step ahead of the fleet.
With the pirate ship destroyed, your ship's system is restored to full functionality. You salvage what you can from the debris.
Upon closer inspection it appears to have a large portion of its hull destroyed. You take what few supplies you can find.
Your scans reveal an ore refinery and several factories, all standing still and empty. No life signs detected.
The outpost hails you, The pompous bastards expected free service just because they defeated the Federation. Take this for the help.
The ship was carrying military supplies. You pick up anything that looks salvageable from the debris.
You have arrived in Engi space. The fall of the Federation has brought tough times for these robotic lifeforms, but they're usually willing to help.
A message arrives: Your scrap, ours. Our weapons for you. You're about to raise the shields when you realize it's just an Engi trader looking for a trade.

column11: The Engi can do remarkable things with just a pile of scrap. The Engi hive at this beacon are selling equipment for just that.
column12: Weapon: LASER CHARGEGUN, BEAM FIRE, BEAM HULL, System: drones, shields, clonebay, Drone: DEFENSE 1, BOARDER ION, COMBAT 1,

column11: The station was either abandoned or stripped clean. It seems to have lain unused for quite some time. You find nothing useful.
You cross paths with an Engi cargo vessel hurrying home before the Mantis fleets attempt to take over this sector. They're happy to offload some of their cargo to get home faster.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
Thank you for your business.
Despite your best efforts, the civilian ship breaks apart from the constant barrage. You are barely able to break out of the asteroid field yourself. The ship sustains some damage in the process.
The words they use are Need = fulfilled, but you take it for gratitude. They take the next jump in their long journey home.
The Zoltan patrol their borders but let you pass when you ID as Federation. Let's hope they won't be so courteous to the Rebels.
Thank you so much! We don't have much to offer, but have a look at the sector scans we took. Your map is updated.
The Zoltan are fascinated by other species, and have set up something of an alien knick-knack shop here. Why not take a look?
column12: Augment: REPAIR ARM, ION ARMOR, TELEPORT HEAL, System: shields, battery, mind, Crew: Slug, Slug, Human,

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
Thank you for rescuing us! They held us hostage to ambush unsuspecting passersby. Please, take this.

They finish: Please, spread the word of enlightenment to those that have not heard. Once you have, contact our brethren. They transmit coordinates of their so-called brethren. Added a quest marker to your map!

Although your methods are crude and most certainly ineffective, it is clear you took our previous meeting to heart. If your ship represents the Federation's willingness to adapt we shall do what we can to aid in their fight. This technology should aid your quest.
They briefly scan your ship and inform you that you are not properly equipped for this type of mission.
A Mantis crew here has hunkered down in the abdomen of a long-dead space-whale - the only way, presumably, for them to operate their black-market trade without detection. Worth a look?

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
A light asteroid field is entering the atmosphere of a nearby planet - a fireworks show on a galactic scale. There's little for it but to take in the ambience and program the next jump.
Thanks to the high nebula density of this sector very little of it has been charted, and rumours of what lurks in the depths abound.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
Your crew are constantly looking out of the windows, checking for hostiles. They jump at every creak and moan of the ship. The tension is almost palpable...
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The station is a storage site for various resources. You salvage everything possible.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

You discover a cluster of Federation refugee ships taking shelter in the folds of the nebula. I'm sorry we've got nothing to give you, but we need scrap to keep the engines running. You sense they'll strike a trade.

Thank you, this will help greatly.
This ship's cargo was not salvageable. However, they seem to have been surveying the region; they possess detailed maps and data. You download what you can to the ship's map.

There is only one other ship at this beacon, and it is showing heavy damage. You receive a message on your console: Greetings traveler. We were crippled by a band of pirates and are now forced to sell our remaining valuable equipment to acquire the necessary supplies to get home.

column11: An abandoned space station circles a lonely planet. A quick check yields schematics for a drone. You bring it aboard the ship.
You will have to be very cautious in this sector. The Rebels have full control and are no doubt looking for you.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
Their ship breaks apart and you are relieved to know that you are still one step ahead of the fleet.
You access the recent scans from the unguarded station. Your map has been updated with details of the surrounding area.
You arrive at a small space station that is putting out wide-band broadcasts on black-market channels. You doubt they would turn away any business, regardless of allegiances.

column11: You arrive near the Federation Base to find the bulk of their fleet skirmishing with Rebel forces. You hang back near the far side of the moon to avoid the conflict. There's not much you can do to help in that battle, and your mission holds the key to turn the tide of the war. You prepare to face the Flagship.
